{"TopicId":222044,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Vessel icons block celestial bodies from being clicked on [when zoomed out] [Vessel Icons have priority over Celestial Bodies]","CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-25T14:21:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-25T14:21:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7-8700 CPU @ 3.20GHz, 6 Core(s), 12 Logical Processor(s) | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Geforce GTX 1070TI | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteps to reproduce:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) Put a vehicle in orbit around any CB, such as Eve.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) Zoom out in the map view and try to right click and select Eve as the target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3) Discover it is impossible because it will always select the vehicle in orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-10T12:51:14Z\u0022 title=\u002202/10/2024 12:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 10\u0022\u003EFebruary 10\u003C/time\u003E by Spicat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ETypo\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-25T15:46:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs a side note, in KSP1 I believe you were able to click on the planets orbit line to select the planet instead, which isn\u0027t possible in KSP2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kaa253","CreatedById":68628,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-29T10:15:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA filter enabling craft to be hidden in map view and tracking station would be very helpfull here. Setting a craft as target when it has nearby debris is equally difficult.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-31T00:07:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0win10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i710700k | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0rtx2060 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32gb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVessel icons, while now small, still block the celestial bodies from being clicked on which makes it odd that the issues weren\u0027t closely connected and fixed at the same time but nevertheless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cvideo class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 controls=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.global.core.embeddedvideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Csource type=\u0022video/mp4\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_01/ico.mp4.c095143a1aee340377e935da2cb72e14.mp4\u0022\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=1322\u0026amp;key=f7fa787bb7aae886df422e5425e16136\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221322\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022mp4\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Eico.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/video\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-01-31T00:09:57Z\u0022 title=\u002201/31/2024 12:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jan 31\u0022\u003EJanuary 31\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T20:55:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly that you can\u0027t hide craft icons in tracking station. Map and tracking station UI is much uncomfortable, I often missclick because\u00A0the cursor sensitivity zones are oddly configured\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astroneer08","CreatedById":223777,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T22:23:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this issue too\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T22:33:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224352893\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703715805\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Astroneer08\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Astroneer08 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this issue too\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClick the arrow at the top of the issue to upvote this and attract the attention of the devs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022RDsaJfc.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022147.66\u0022 height=\u0022158\u0022 width=\u0022107\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/RDsaJfc.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astroneer08","CreatedById":223777,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T23:07:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T01:56:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs a shameless plug, there is a mod i created specifically as a workaround for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2938362182\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/216073-mapview-focus-and-targeting/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPage Up/Down to cycle through celestial bodies in the Kerbolar System, \u002B/- to target or remove target, and Home to reset the focus to the currently controlled craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bc2307","CreatedById":231845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T13:44:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame with Minmus. For a mission you have to put a satellite in orbit around Minmus, but good luck setting Minmus as target for the next mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-01T16:18:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis bug is incredibly annoying.. it forces the player to scroll SO MUCH.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-31T00:12:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/150811-the-aziz/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150811\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/